============================================================
PYTHON PART 1 – EXPLORATORY DATA ANALYSIS (EDA)
============================================================

Description:
This section represents the first Python phase of the
project and focuses on Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
and data visualization using the structured outputs
generated from the SQL analytics workflow.

The datasets used in this phase are the final analytical
CSV summaries produced in Section 04 of the SQL module.
These files contain cleaned, aggregated, and analysis-ready
football statistics covering:
- overall dataset information
- team performance metrics
- matchup statistics between teams

Using Python libraries such as:
- pandas
- matplotlib
- seaborn

the data is loaded, explored, analyzed, and transformed
into visual representations to extract meaningful football
analytics insights.

The purpose of this phase is to:
- validate the structured SQL outputs
- explore statistical patterns
- visualize relationships between metrics
- identify team and matchup behavior
- transform numerical summaries into interpretable insights


------------------------------------------------------------
Analytical Workflow
------------------------------------------------------------

The Python EDA workflow is organized into three main
analytical sections:

01_general
Provides a high-level overview of the dataset through
dashboard-style visualizations, focusing on:
- dataset size
- scoring behavior
- match outcomes
- discipline statistics

This stage establishes the analytical context of the
project and summarizes the overall characteristics of
the dataset.


02_team_perf
Focuses on team-level analysis using ranking charts,
scatter plots, and correlation heatmaps.

The analysis examines:
- total wins
- win rate
- goals scored and conceded
- goal difference
- home vs away performance
- relationships between performance metrics

This section helps identify:
- dominant teams
- offensive and defensive profiles
- efficiency patterns
- competitive consistency across seasons


03_matchup
Analyzes direct head-to-head matchups between selected
Big 5 Premier League clubs:
- Arsenal
- Manchester City
- Manchester United
- Chelsea
- Liverpool

The analysis focuses on:
- scoring behavior
- rivalry intensity
- win dominance
- offensive activity
- physical match characteristics

Heatmaps and comparison charts are used to highlight
differences in playing style and competitiveness between
elite teams.


------------------------------------------------------------
Key Analytical Insights
------------------------------------------------------------

The visual analysis reveals several important football
performance patterns:

- Strong teams consistently combine high attacking output
  with solid defensive performance.

- Goal difference demonstrates a strong relationship with
  overall success and win rate.

- Home advantage remains a significant factor across
  Premier League matches.

- Elite team matchups display different competitive
  behaviors:
  - some rivalries are highly offensive and high-scoring
  - others are more physical and defensively balanced

- Correlation analysis confirms that successful teams
  maintain balanced performance across multiple metrics,
  including scoring efficiency and defensive stability.


